<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-517-818  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 517 818.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 1 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Audiotex system business brisk.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Brite Systems (securities).andO;Topic:     Computer industryMarket AnalysisNetworksPublic OfferingsAudio Visual.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>AUDIOTEX SYSTEM BUSINESS BRISK WICHITA, KANSAS, U.S.A., 1989 JUL 24 (NB) --The booming business of providing audiotex services has been matched by aboom in equipment to provide such services.andP;  Brite Systems, which producessuch systems based on Sperry hardware, is preparing an initial publicoffering after benefitting from this boom.andP;  Tad Snarenberger, a salesman forthe company, says newspapers and local TV stations are snapping up the BriteSystem, which consists of Sperry or Panasonic PCs running a non-DOS operatingsystem called QNX.andP;  Marketing Director Brian Schoenthaler said pricing isbased on the number of ports, number of hours of storage, type of nodes andthe software used, with small systems available for $40-50,000 and thelargest running over $1 million.andP;  The company filed an S-1 and proxystatement in mid-July indicating sales for this year could double last year's$38 million.andP;  (Dana Blankenhorn/19890728/Press Contact: Tad Snarenberger,316- 687-4444, FAX: 316-687-6838)</TEXT></DOC>